Hey, thank you. I feel really great.

75
00:05:02.700 --> 00:05:03.741
Yeah.

76
00:05:03.825 --> 00:05:07.283
I mean, they must pay you
a lot of money in this place.

77
00:05:07.366 --> 00:05:08.908
- You know what?
- You're really good.

78
00:05:08.991 --> 00:05:11.783
I tell you what, I feel like
a million dollars, never felt so good.

79
00:05:11.866 --> 00:05:14.700
I'm gonna see myself out. Thank you.
Doctor! No, you're not...

80
00:05:14.783 --> 00:05:17.741
You're gonna release that monster...
He's gonna destroy everything!

81
00:05:17.825 --> 00:05:20.325
- He's gonna destroy everything!
- Be gentle with him!

82
00:05:20.408 --> 00:05:22.241
Listen, I am not your enemy!

83
00:05:22.325 --> 00:05:24.575
No! No!

84
00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:26.033
(BOTH SCREAMING)

85
00:05:27.116 --> 00:05:28.200
Hippo! Hippo!

86
00:05:28.283 --> 00:05:29.658
Oh, man!

87
00:05:30.033 --> 00:05:31.866
Wow, these meds are really amazing.

88
00:05:32.575 --> 00:05:34.950
Is he always so intense?

89
00:05:35.033 --> 00:05:36.991
Who, him? Yeah, pretty much.

90
00:05:37.950 --> 00:05:39.616
HIPPO: So, are you two, like, twins?

91
00:05:39.950 --> 00:05:41.325
- No.
- Well, yes, sort of.

92
00:05:41.408 --> 00:05:43.033
HIPPO: Okay, great.

93
00:05:43.116 --> 00:05:45.366
That's really cleared this
whole situation up for me.

94
00:05:45.450 --> 00:05:46.450
That makes two of us.

95
00:05:46.575 --> 00:05:48.991
Just a second ago,
I thought I'd been shot to death.

96
00:05:49.075 --> 00:05:51.866
Oh, gosh!
This will really bake your noodle,

97
00:05:51.950 --> 00:05:54.158
but I think you were just taking
a little time-out.

98
00:05:54.866 --> 00:05:56.866
I'm afraid you're actually quite dead.

99
00:05:57.366 --> 00:05:58.450
I'm sorry, what?

100
00:05:59.741 --> 00:06:00.741
But...

101
00:06:01.825 --> 00:06:03.366
I'm dead? We're dead?

102
00:06:03.616 --> 00:06:04.616
Yes.

103
00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:07.533
Yes, Marc. I think she's right.

104
00:06:07.616 --> 00:06:10.116
I think we died.

105
00:06:11.116 --> 00:06:14.075
HIPPO: I actually... I have...
Hold on a sec.

106
00:06:14.283 --> 00:06:16.825
It's been a minute
since we've had a soul pass through here.

107
00:06:16.908 --> 00:06:20.700
Bit distracted... Excuse me.

108
00:06:22.366 --> 00:06:25.158
A-ha! Okay, here we go.

109
00:06:31.158 --> 00:06:35.200
Welcome, gentle traveler... Travelers,

110
00:06:35.491 --> 00:06:37.658
to the realm of the Duat.

111
00:06:37.741 --> 00:06:40.075
Duat? The Egyptian underworld.

112
00:06:40.616 --> 00:06:41.866
This is Taweret,

113
00:06:41.950 --> 00:06:44.408
- goddess of women and children...
- MARC: Uh-huh.

114
00:06:44.575 --> 00:06:48.033
...and she's guiding us through
our journey to the afterlife.

115
00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:50.325
- Wow.
- MARC: Okay.

116
00:06:51.325 --> 00:06:56.325
Right. So, this is the afterlife?

117
00:06:56.575 --> 00:07:00.991
- The afterlife?
- An afterlife. Not the afterlife.

118
00:07:01.325 --> 00:07:03.700
You'd be surprised how many
intersectional planes

119
00:07:03.783 --> 00:07:06.075
- of untethered consciousness exist.
- Yeah.

120
00:07:06.283 --> 00:07:10.866
(GASPS) Like the Ancestral Plane.
Oh! Just gorgeous. Anyway.

121
00:07:10.950 --> 00:07:13.491
I do actually have cards for all this

122
00:07:13.575 --> 00:07:16.741
if you just wait, and... I'm sorry.

123
00:07:17.241 --> 00:07:18.408
Wait... Bye.

124
00:07:18.575 --> 00:07:20.075
(GASPS SOFTLY) Okay, so...

125
00:07:22.158 --> 00:07:25.866
Because the Duat's true nature
is impossible for the human mind

126
00:07:25.950 --> 00:07:27.033
- to comprehend...
- Right.

127
00:07:27.116 --> 00:07:29.908
...you may perceive this realm
as something

128
00:07:29.991 --> 00:07:31.825
more easily recognizable to you.

129
00:07:32.241 --> 00:07:35.241
- Uh-huh.
- A psych ward's a first for me,

130
00:07:35.325 --> 00:07:38.366
but, hey, we can roll with it, right?

131
00:07:39.366 --> 00:07:42.616
Why would we imagine this realm
to be a psychiatric hospital?

132
00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:44.408
Because we're insane.

133
00:07:45.200 --> 00:07:46.533
(MARC EXHALES)

134
00:07:50.158 --> 00:07:51.575
We're insane.

135
00:07:52.533 --> 00:07:53.658
This talking hippo,

136
00:07:54.366 --> 00:07:58.033
talking dead bird,
you're outside of my body now.

137
00:07:58.116 --> 00:08:00.200
And now the afterlife, right?

138
00:08:00.283 --> 00:08:03.283
- That's the reality and this...
- STEVEN: But Marc, Marc.

139
00:08:03.366 --> 00:08:07.283
The hospital. That's the imagination.

140
00:08:08.325 --> 00:08:11.783
- Sorry, he's...
- Oh, man. Dr. Harrow's right.

141
00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:13.366
Dr. Harrow?

142
00:08:14.408 --> 00:08:16.033
This is an organizing principle.

143
00:08:16.116 --> 00:08:18.325
- Is he a doctor now?
- MARC: I'll prove it you.

144
00:08:18.408 --> 00:08:21.325
So, like, right through these doors,
for example,

145
00:08:21.408 --> 00:08:23.533
we go through here,
there's gonna be patients,

146
00:08:23.616 --> 00:08:26.950
and there's Crawley
probably about to yell bingo!

147
00:08:27.200 --> 00:08:28.533
Oh, my God!

148
00:08:29.158 --> 00:08:30.200
Oh, my God!

149
00:08:37.741 --> 00:08:38.866
What is this?

150
00:08:38.950 --> 00:08:40.200
This is the underworld.

151
00:08:40.908 --> 00:08:42.158
I'm not crazy.

152
00:08:42.783 --> 00:08:43.783
I'm dead.

153
00:08:43.866 --> 00:08:46.700
- Where did you say we're going?
- We're sailing to A'aru.

154
00:08:47.033 --> 00:08:49.616
To the Field of Reeds, right, Taweret?

155
00:08:49.700 --> 00:08:51.658
Ah, so he's the smart one, hey?

156
00:08:51.741 --> 00:08:56.616
Well, if your heart's balanced in life,
then you will spend eternity in paradise.

157
00:08:57.200 --> 00:08:58.575
The Field of Reeds.

158
00:08:58.991 --> 00:09:03.783
But before we get there,
I've just got to do a quick little...

159
00:09:06.533 --> 00:09:09.950
- Whoa! Easy! Easy, easy, easy there!
- (TAWERET GASPS)

160
00:09:11.116 --> 00:09:13.866
Oh, goody! It worked! Look at that!

161
00:09:14.200 --> 00:09:17.866
Here was little old me worrying I'd blow
your chests wide open.

162
00:09:17.950 --> 00:09:19.241
STEVEN: Sorry, what?

163
00:09:19.866 --> 00:09:21.033
MARC: Wait, what's she doing?

164
00:09:21.116 --> 00:09:24.408
STEVEN: She's weighing our hearts
on the Scales of Justice

165
00:09:24.491 --> 00:09:25.783
and the Feather of Truth.

166
00:09:25.866 --> 00:09:28.575
You see, the ancient Egyptians believed
that the heart

167
00:09:28.658 --> 00:09:31.325
was the sign of
who you really were in life.

168
00:09:31.783 --> 00:09:34.700
If the Scales balance
by the time you end the journey,

169
00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:37.658
then a soul is permitted to pass
into the Field of Reeds.

170
00:09:38.033 --> 00:09:41.450
- MARC: What if they don't balance?
- You get thrown overboard. Whoo!

171
00:09:42.366 --> 00:09:44.158
The dead will drag you down into the Duat,

172
00:09:44.241 --> 00:09:47.366
where you will remain forever,
frozen in sand.

173
00:09:48.158 --> 00:09:51.616
No unbalanced souls on my boat.
Them's the rules.

174
00:09:51.825 --> 00:09:53.616
Fingers crossed for you guys, hey?

175
00:09:55.241 --> 00:09:58.616
I don't care what this hippo says.
There's no way we're ending up down there.

176
00:09:58.700 --> 00:10:00.825
And we're not going to
the Field of Reeds, either.

177
00:10:00.908 --> 00:10:03.658
- All right. What are you proposing?
- If it comes to it,

178
00:10:04.825 --> 00:10:06.491
kill the hippo, steal the boat.

179
00:10:06.575 --> 00:10:07.575
Kill?

180
00:10:08.366 --> 00:10:10.158
- Um, fellas?
- (MACHINERY RUSTLING)

181
00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:16.700
What? Why is it doing that?
Why is it moving like that?

182
00:10:16.783 --> 00:10:21.116
TAWERET: I don't know.
I do not have a card for this.

183
00:10:25.616 --> 00:10:27.783
Oh. It's the hearts.

184
00:10:28.408 --> 00:10:30.408
They aren't full.

185
00:10:30.533 --> 00:10:33.491
And trust me, I'm a goblet half-full
kind of gal, but...

186
00:10:34.116 --> 00:10:36.075
It's like they each feel incomplete.

187
00:10:36.158 --> 00:10:37.241
What does that mean?

188
00:10:37.325 --> 00:10:41.325
Without balanced Scales,
the Duat will eventually claim your soul.

189
00:10:42.575 --> 00:10:44.283
Do you have any other suggestions?

190
00:10:45.741 --> 00:10:48.200
This boat contains
all of a life's memories.

191
00:10:48.283 --> 00:10:51.658
Now I don't know what you two guys
have been hiding, but my advice,

192
00:10:51.908 --> 00:10:54.450
get in there
and show each other the truth.

193
00:10:54.658 --> 00:10:57.741
Balance your Scales before
we arrive at the Field of Reeds,

194
00:10:57.908 --> 00:11:00.033
or your souls will be destroyed.

195
00:11:00.366 --> 00:11:03.200
- STEVEN: Yeah, all right.
- So how are we supposed to do this?

196
00:11:03.658 --> 00:11:06.616
Not sure. You think Layla's all right?

197
00:11:07.366 --> 00:11:08.616
Yeah, for now.

198
00:11:09.116 --> 00:11:12.658
And knowing her, she'll go on
a suicide mission to stop Harrow herself.

199
00:11:13.408 --> 00:11:15.241
That means we better hurry, doesn't it?

200
00:11:15.325 --> 00:11:17.241
Know what Layla would be all right with?

201
00:11:17.325 --> 00:11:19.741
- Don't. Just don't say it.
- I'm just saying there is

202
00:11:19.825 --> 00:11:21.366
one hippo and two of us,

203
00:11:21.450 --> 00:11:23.658
and this ship can't be
that hard to steer. So...

204
00:11:23.741 --> 00:11:27.033
- And we don't have to actually...
- Have to what? Kill the Goddess Taweret?

205
00:11:27.116 --> 00:11:29.241
No, just, you know, find me a rope and...

206
00:11:29.325 --> 00:11:31.033
Yeah. Or we can do what she says,

207
00:11:31.116 --> 00:11:34.491
and help each other uncover whatever it is
that we're hiding, apparently.

208
00:11:34.575 --> 00:11:38.783
Steven, I don't know about you,
but my memories are a fricking mess.

209
00:11:38.950 --> 00:11:41.575
- Yeah, mine, too.
- (MAN GRUNTING)

210
00:11:55.991 --> 00:11:57.075
MARC: Whoa.

211
00:11:57.950 --> 00:11:58.991
That's wild.

212
00:12:05.033 --> 00:12:06.075
STEVEN: Oi. What's this?

213
00:12:06.158 --> 00:12:07.700
Steven, what are we gonna do here?

214
00:12:07.783 --> 00:12:10.283
We're gonna
revisit every single memory I've ever had?

215
00:12:12.783 --> 00:12:14.908
Do you... Do you remember this?

216
00:12:17.325 --> 00:12:19.991
Yeah. I don't know,
it's just a street, you know.

217
00:12:20.075 --> 00:12:22.366
How many streets
have you walked down your whole life?

218
00:12:23.950 --> 00:12:25.866
BOY: Help!

219
00:12:26.741 --> 00:12:27.866
Did you hear that?

220
00:12:33.908 --> 00:12:34.908
MARC: Hey.

221
00:12:39.408 --> 00:12:42.533
STEVEN: Just a creepy caff
filled with dead bodies.

222
00:12:42.616 --> 00:12:46.366
That's all it is. No prizes guessing
whose room this is.

223
00:12:46.991 --> 00:12:48.450
- Yours.
- Funny.

224
00:13:05.658 --> 00:13:06.658
Dubai.

225
00:13:10.200 --> 00:13:11.325
Gabon.

226
00:13:15.783 --> 00:13:17.908
New York. No way.

227
00:13:17.991 --> 00:13:19.075
Oh, man.

228
00:13:19.283 --> 00:13:21.075
STEVEN: What, do you know these people?

229
00:13:22.491 --> 00:13:24.366
No. Oh, no.

230
00:13:24.533 --> 00:13:27.783
Surely not all of them?

231
00:13:28.616 --> 00:13:30.575
You killed all of them?

232
00:13:31.325 --> 00:13:35.241
They were criminals. Murderers. Predators.
The worst of the worst.

233
00:13:35.325 --> 00:13:36.700
Khonshu wanted them punished.

234
00:13:36.783 --> 00:13:39.616
It's what he meant by
protecting the travelers of the night.

235
00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:41.533
STEVEN: And you remember each person?

236
00:13:41.616 --> 00:13:42.991
You try taking a life.

237
00:13:45.491 --> 00:13:46.866
See how quickly you forget.

238
00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:53.033
Kept wishing I'd fail
and one of them would kill me instead.

239
00:13:54.658 --> 00:13:57.241
- The healing ended up being a curse.
- Marc!

240
00:13:57.616 --> 00:13:58.866
Do you see this? Look.

241
00:13:59.366 --> 00:14:01.991
The Scales are slowing down. It's working.

242
00:14:02.075 --> 00:14:05.908
Okay, all right. So then, now what?
What do we do? Do you go next?

243
00:14:05.991 --> 00:14:07.366
Um... Who's that?

244
00:14:14.366 --> 00:14:15.366
Marc,

245
00:14:16.533 --> 00:14:20.741
why is there a child in a room filled
with people that you've killed?

246
00:14:22.491 --> 00:14:25.116
- Steven, look, don't go near him.
- Hey, little man.

247
00:14:26.533 --> 00:14:28.616
What's your name, there?
Oh, hold on there.

248
00:14:28.700 --> 00:14:30.783
- Wait a moment.
- Steven. Wait! Wait!

249
00:14:34.408 --> 00:14:35.991
Come on! No, wait! Steven! Steven!

250
00:14:38.491 --> 00:14:41.491
Open the door! Open the door!

251
00:14:46.283 --> 00:14:47.991
- Open the door!
- Mom?

252
00:14:49.783 --> 00:14:52.575
Food's ready. Who's hungry? RoRo?

253
00:14:52.658 --> 00:14:54.200
Mom, come check out my drawing.

254
00:14:54.283 --> 00:14:56.241
YOUNG MARC: He drew the fish
with only one fin.

255
00:14:56.325 --> 00:14:58.200
Marc, be nice to your little brother.

256
00:14:58.783 --> 00:14:59.950
I had a brother?

257
00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:03.241
I'm not hungry. Want to go to the cave?

258
00:15:04.491 --> 00:15:05.866
We'll eat later.

259
00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:08.408
Boys? Don't be gone too long.

260
00:15:08.741 --> 00:15:11.366
Hey, hey, hey, Marc. What do you do?

261
00:15:11.950 --> 00:15:14.033
Keep an eye on your brother. Okay?

262
00:15:14.408 --> 00:15:15.533
Laters, gators.

263
00:15:15.825 --> 00:15:17.408
In a while, crocodile.

264
00:15:22.908 --> 00:15:24.158
(MARC PANTING)

265
00:15:24.241 --> 00:15:25.616
Where'd they go?

266
00:15:26.658 --> 00:15:28.158
Let's do it. Let's go.

267
00:15:28.825 --> 00:15:31.116
RANDALL: Okay. Okay, okay, fine, but...

268
00:15:31.616 --> 00:15:33.033
I'll be Rosser, though.

269
00:15:33.866 --> 00:15:35.950
(IN BRITISH ACCENT)
Can you hear that, Dr. Grant?

270
00:15:36.075 --> 00:15:37.658
(IN BRITISH ACCENT) I sure do, Rosser.

271
00:15:37.783 --> 00:15:39.908
Sounds to me like danger.

272
00:15:40.533 --> 00:15:42.908
- Dr. Grant?
- (THUNDER RUMBLES)

273
00:15:43.033 --> 00:15:44.967
(IN NORMAL VOICE)
Mom said not to when it's raining.

274
00:15:44.991 --> 00:15:46.911
(IN NORMAL VOICE)
It'll be fine. Don't be a baby.

275
00:16:01.866 --> 00:16:03.450
RANDALL: That was awesome.

276
00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:07.325
Oh.

277
00:16:16.991 --> 00:16:18.366
(MARC PANTING)

278
00:16:19.533 --> 00:16:21.033
Oh, God. Oh, no.

279
00:16:22.533 --> 00:16:23.533
Lads?

280
00:16:24.533 --> 00:16:26.158
You have to get out of here!

281
00:16:27.825 --> 00:16:29.116
Boys?

282
00:16:30.408 --> 00:16:31.825
Don't go any further!

283
00:16:32.283 --> 00:16:34.325
The water's rising way too fast!

284
00:16:35.700 --> 00:16:37.325
You got to get out of here.

285
00:16:39.408 --> 00:16:40.408
Boys?

286
00:16:41.366 --> 00:16:42.783
Where are they?

287
00:16:45.491 --> 00:16:47.783
MARC: Steven? Come back here!

288
00:16:49.075 --> 00:16:50.200
STEVEN: Boys?

289
00:16:52.033 --> 00:16:54.950
Come on, lads. We have to leave now!

290
00:16:55.116 --> 00:16:57.575
Can you hear me? Can you hear me?

291
00:16:58.658 --> 00:17:00.075
- Where are you?
- (MARC GASPS)

292
00:17:00.700 --> 00:17:02.241
STEVEN: Marc! Marc!

293
00:17:03.075 --> 00:17:05.366
- Help us, please! Help us.
- Marc! Oh, God.

294
00:17:05.450 --> 00:17:07.658
- YOUNG MARC: RoRo!
- Follow my voice!

295
00:17:07.825 --> 00:17:09.241
- Boys!
- RANDALL: Mommy!

296
00:17:09.325 --> 00:17:11.616
- Mommy! I want my mommy!
- MARC: No. No, no, no.

297
00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:13.241
STEVEN: I hear you!

298
00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:14.801
- RANDALL: Mommy!
- I hear you, Marc!

299
00:17:14.825 --> 00:17:15.950
YOUNG MARC: RoRo!

300
00:17:16.991 --> 00:17:19.491
- It's just a memory. It is just a memory.
- Help!

301
00:17:19.575 --> 00:17:20.975
- RANDALL: Mommy!
- Damn it, Steven.

302
00:17:30.575 --> 00:17:31.908
(DOOR HANDLE CLICKS)

303
00:17:35.075 --> 00:17:36.283
(DOOR HINGES CREAKING)

304
00:17:59.825 --> 00:18:01.283
Hey, Steven.

305
00:18:02.741 --> 00:18:04.533
WENDY: I want my RoRo back.

306
00:18:07.241 --> 00:18:10.325
I want him back.

307
00:18:11.450 --> 00:18:12.783
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

308
00:18:22.575 --> 00:18:24.991
What are you doing here? Hmm?

309
00:18:27.241 --> 00:18:28.283
MARC: Come on, buddy.

310
00:18:29.116 --> 00:18:30.783
You were supposed to keep him safe!

311
00:18:30.866 --> 00:18:31.908
Steven, let's go.

312
00:18:34.366 --> 00:18:36.116
WENDY: You let him drown.

313
00:18:36.908 --> 00:18:40.241
This is all your fault!

314
00:18:40.366 --> 00:18:43.241
This is all your fault!

315
00:18:45.033 --> 00:18:46.616
- (SOBBING)
- Hey, Steven. Come here.

316
00:18:47.158 --> 00:18:49.450
Come here! Stop, stop! Don't go up there!

317
00:18:49.866 --> 00:18:50.866
Stop!

318
00:18:50.950 --> 00:18:53.366
ELIAS: Wendy? Wendy, come on, please.

319
00:18:55.700 --> 00:18:56.741
Wendy, please.

320
00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:01.366
We're just about to blow out
the candles now.

321
00:19:07.283 --> 00:19:08.325
She's not coming.

322
00:19:11.783 --> 00:19:13.575
Your mother's not feeling well, Marc.

323
00:19:15.116 --> 00:19:17.866
We'll do it just you and I this year.

324
00:19:18.450 --> 00:19:19.491
Okay?

325
00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:31.200
MARC: Steven!

326
00:19:33.533 --> 00:19:34.533
Steven!

327
00:19:40.158 --> 00:19:42.783
You can't have a birthday
without your favorite cake!

328
00:19:42.866 --> 00:19:44.116
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

329
00:19:44.533 --> 00:19:46.241
Get started on these, okay, son?

330
00:19:49.700 --> 00:19:51.616
WENDY: You were always jealous of him.

331
00:19:51.700 --> 00:19:52.950
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

332
00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:57.075
Ever since he was born.

333
00:20:02.908 --> 00:20:04.033
I...

334
00:20:04.116 --> 00:20:07.366
I should've known
you would do something like this.

335
00:20:10.075 --> 00:20:11.075
(CLATTERS)

336
00:20:13.241 --> 00:20:14.658
Mum, what are you doing?

337
00:20:20.658 --> 00:20:21.658
MARC: Steven!

338
00:20:28.491 --> 00:20:29.700
(GASPS)

339
00:20:30.408 --> 00:20:32.408
What happened in that room, Marc?

340
00:20:33.283 --> 00:20:35.741
- That's it, Steven. That's it.
- All right! All right.

341
00:20:36.700 --> 00:20:38.325
Why are you remembering her like that?

342
00:20:38.408 --> 00:20:39.991
That's not what she was like.

343
00:20:41.366 --> 00:20:44.075
No. Let me go. Let me back in there.
What are you hiding?

344
00:20:44.158 --> 00:20:45.491
What are you hiding?

345
00:20:45.575 --> 00:20:48.158
ELIAS: Marc, son. Please come inside.

346
00:20:48.866 --> 00:20:49.991
She will get help.

347
00:20:50.075 --> 00:20:51.075
Dad.

348
00:20:51.158 --> 00:20:54.033
- We will fix this.
- You're supposed to fix this.

349
00:20:54.116 --> 00:20:56.825
I mean... Why haven't you?

350
00:20:57.408 --> 00:20:58.408
(GRUNTS)

351
00:21:00.866 --> 00:21:02.366
I cannot lose another son.

352
00:21:02.825 --> 00:21:03.908
Please.

353
00:21:06.491 --> 00:21:07.658
Please...

354
00:21:08.825 --> 00:21:10.241
MARC: That's enough, Steven.

355
00:21:11.616 --> 00:21:12.866
Get off me!

356
00:21:13.616 --> 00:21:14.700
(STEVEN SPITS)

357
00:21:17.991 --> 00:21:19.491
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

358
00:21:21.450 --> 00:21:22.825
Where the hell are we now?

359
00:21:29.533 --> 00:21:30.616
Oh, God.

360
00:21:34.158 --> 00:21:37.241
- (SIGHS)
- Harrow said you were a mercenary.

361
00:21:40.241 --> 00:21:43.283
That you killed hostages.

362
00:21:45.283 --> 00:21:47.991
- And you believe that?
- Yeah. Wouldn't put it past you.

363
00:21:53.241 --> 00:21:55.075
MARC: Turns out going AWOL
in a fugue state

364
00:21:55.158 --> 00:21:56.908
gets you discharged from the military.

365
00:21:57.033 --> 00:21:58.866
Didn't have a ton of options after that,

366
00:21:58.950 --> 00:22:01.116
so I went work-for-hire
for my old CO Bushman.

367
00:22:01.866 --> 00:22:03.866
The job was to raid an Egyptian tomb.

368
00:22:05.075 --> 00:22:06.325
But Bushman changed the plan,

369
00:22:07.283 --> 00:22:09.533
called for no witnesses,
and I couldn't live with that.

370
00:22:09.700 --> 00:22:11.658
STEVEN: Is that Doctor El Faouly?

371
00:22:11.783 --> 00:22:12.908
Layla's dad?

372
00:22:15.366 --> 00:22:18.283
(SIGHS) I tried to get them all away.

373
00:22:20.491 --> 00:22:21.491
But we didn't make it.

374
00:22:23.283 --> 00:22:24.325
Clearly.

375
00:22:25.325 --> 00:22:26.700
What happened to you?

376
00:23:03.325 --> 00:23:04.325
(GRUNTING)

377
00:23:05.450 --> 00:23:06.491
(GROANS)

378
00:23:25.575 --> 00:23:27.575
KHONSHU: What a waste.

379
00:23:28.075 --> 00:23:29.283
(KHONSHU SCOFFS)

380
00:23:29.908 --> 00:23:30.991
Huh?

381
00:23:31.408 --> 00:23:34.741
I feel the pain inside of you.

382
00:23:35.616 --> 00:23:36.616
Ah.

383
00:23:37.575 --> 00:23:38.658
Hmm.

384
00:23:39.366 --> 00:23:42.283
What the hell are you?

385
00:23:43.325 --> 00:23:46.158
I am the god Khonshu,

386
00:23:46.450 --> 00:23:48.950
in search of a warrior.

387
00:23:49.283 --> 00:23:51.450
MARC: (SCOFFS) A warrior.

388
00:23:51.991 --> 00:23:53.491
Well, good luck with that.

389
00:23:53.950 --> 00:23:58.866
KHONSHU: To be my hands,
my eyes, my vengeance.

390
00:23:59.741 --> 00:24:03.991
To be my final word against the evildoers.

391
00:24:04.075 --> 00:24:07.533
To bind your very being to me

392
00:24:07.658 --> 00:24:12.950
and eradicate only the worst,
those who deserve it.

393
00:24:13.241 --> 00:24:14.908
Do you want death

394
00:24:15.866 --> 00:24:17.283
or do you want life?

395
00:24:19.116 --> 00:24:20.325
I don't know.

396
00:24:20.741 --> 00:24:26.741
Your mind, I feel it. Fractured. Broken.

397
00:24:27.575 --> 00:24:29.366
Most fascinating.

398
00:24:30.283 --> 00:24:35.491
You are a worthy candidate
to serve me during this time.

399
00:24:37.491 --> 00:24:39.783
In exchange for your life,

400
00:24:40.700 --> 00:24:44.325
do you swear to protect
the travelers of the night

401
00:24:45.200 --> 00:24:49.825
and bring my vengeance to those
who would do them harm?

402
00:24:49.908 --> 00:24:51.783
STEVEN: That sneaky old vulture.

403
00:24:53.075 --> 00:24:55.116
He was manipulating you from the start.

404
00:24:55.200 --> 00:24:56.950
MARC: Yeah, well, he kept us alive.

405
00:24:57.325 --> 00:25:00.075
STEVEN: Marc,
he was taking advantage of you.

406
00:25:00.825 --> 00:25:04.033
Or it was just a way for me
to keep being what I've always been.

407
00:25:05.283 --> 00:25:06.283
A killer.

408
00:25:07.200 --> 00:25:12.408
KHONSHU: Do you swear to protect
the travelers of the night

409
00:25:12.491 --> 00:25:17.075
and bring my vengeance
to those who would do them harm?

410
00:25:20.158 --> 00:25:21.158
Yes.

411
00:25:21.325 --> 00:25:22.616
Look.

412
00:25:23.616 --> 00:25:24.741
The Scales.

413
00:25:26.033 --> 00:25:28.116
Have we done it? Have we balanced them?

414
00:25:30.741 --> 00:25:32.200
KHONSHU: Then rise.

415
00:25:32.533 --> 00:25:34.866
Rise and live again.

416
00:25:34.950 --> 00:25:37.658
As my fist of vengeance.

417
00:25:38.366 --> 00:25:39.950
As my

418
00:25:40.575 --> 00:25:42.575
Moon Knight.

419
00:25:48.158 --> 00:25:50.033
- (CREATURES SCREECHING)
- Are those...

420
00:25:51.450 --> 00:25:53.450
Come on, Marc. Let's go!

421
00:25:55.866 --> 00:25:57.116
Taweret, what's going on?

422
00:25:57.200 --> 00:25:59.000
TAWERET: Fear is spreading
in the upper world.

423
00:25:59.075 --> 00:26:02.700
Unbalanced souls are being judged or
condemned to the sands before their time.

424
00:26:02.783 --> 00:26:05.366
Oh, this is bad. This is evil.

425
00:26:05.450 --> 00:26:08.283
- Harrow.
- You see why we have to go back?

426
00:26:09.116 --> 00:26:11.241
TAWERET: Even if I could
send you back up there,

427
00:26:11.325 --> 00:26:13.783
you'd just be returning to a body
with a bullet in it.

428
00:26:13.866 --> 00:26:15.158
You wouldn't be able to heal.

429
00:26:15.241 --> 00:26:18.158
STEVEN: Can you send word to Layla?
Please. Help us free Khonshu.

430
00:26:18.241 --> 00:26:20.366
Are you sure
you want to be with Khonshu again?

431
00:26:20.450 --> 00:26:22.658
Seems like you really want
to get away from him.

432
00:26:22.741 --> 00:26:25.950
I did, but this is our only shot.
It's the way it's gotta be.

433
00:26:26.075 --> 00:26:27.700
Please, Taweret, you have to help us.

434
00:26:28.241 --> 00:26:29.283
Please.

435
00:26:31.158 --> 00:26:32.408
What the heck?

436
00:26:32.700 --> 00:26:34.783
Osiris is not going to like this,

437
00:26:34.866 --> 00:26:37.366
but his gate is the only path back.

438
00:26:38.241 --> 00:26:39.575
(TAWERET GRUNTING)

439
00:26:45.741 --> 00:26:49.116
Get back inside! You don't have long.

440
00:26:49.200 --> 00:26:51.741
Get those Scales balanced.

441
00:26:52.658 --> 00:26:54.033
(TAWERET PANTING)

442
00:27:00.991 --> 00:27:03.866
STEVEN: There was that bedroom
that you didn't want me to go into.

443
00:27:03.950 --> 00:27:06.075
- That's it. That's where we'll go.
- Just a second.

444
00:27:06.158 --> 00:27:08.741
Just wait a second.
Just give me a second here. Okay?

445
00:27:08.866 --> 00:27:12.700
Um, look, we don't have to
go back through it all again.

446
00:27:12.783 --> 00:27:14.575
We can just talk. Let's just talk.

447
00:27:14.741 --> 00:27:16.575
Right here, right now. I'll tell you...

448
00:27:16.658 --> 00:27:18.241
I'll tell you everything. Okay?

449
00:27:19.033 --> 00:27:22.116
I'm just begging you,
don't make us go there again.

450
00:27:22.200 --> 00:27:23.408
It's not worth it.

451
00:27:23.491 --> 00:27:24.950
Not worth it?

452
00:27:26.200 --> 00:27:28.783
Not worth it?
Marc, you're about to lose everything.

453
00:27:29.491 --> 00:27:30.658
Do you understand?

454
00:27:31.283 --> 00:27:34.575
If we don't get back, and Harrow succeeds,

455
00:27:34.658 --> 00:27:37.408
and all those people die...

456
00:27:37.741 --> 00:27:39.991
If Layla dies,

457
00:27:40.075 --> 00:27:41.658
that's on your head.

458
00:27:42.158 --> 00:27:43.491
It'll be all your fault.

459
00:27:43.575 --> 00:27:46.825
No, no, no! You can't! I won't do it!

460
00:27:46.908 --> 00:27:50.658
I won't do it! You can't make me!
You can't make me!

461
00:27:50.741 --> 00:27:52.825
Marc. Marc. Marc.

462
00:27:52.908 --> 00:27:54.075
Stop it. Stop it.

463
00:27:54.158 --> 00:27:55.533
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

464
00:28:05.200 --> 00:28:06.950
Did you inject me with something?

465
00:28:09.283 --> 00:28:13.741
You watch too many movies,
all right? (CHUCKLES)

466
00:28:13.908 --> 00:28:16.908
We can't involuntarily sedate patients.

467
00:28:16.991 --> 00:28:20.325
Not these days, huh?
I mean, not unless absolutely necessary.

468
00:28:21.991 --> 00:28:26.158
Oh, Marc, what you've been doing
is so difficult.

469
00:28:26.491 --> 00:28:27.866
I'm so proud of you.

470
00:28:28.741 --> 00:28:33.158
Reliving these kind of
traumatic memories can be so painful.

471
00:28:33.241 --> 00:28:35.575
They look and feel so real,

472
00:28:35.658 --> 00:28:38.741
and you have been at it for hours.

473
00:28:39.741 --> 00:28:40.950
Great work.

474
00:28:41.908 --> 00:28:44.283
It's really... You've been peering inward,

475
00:28:44.700 --> 00:28:49.033
looking deeply into all of the moments
that make you, you.

476
00:28:49.866 --> 00:28:52.325
Here. Come on. Take it.

477
00:28:52.533 --> 00:28:55.450
Yeah. I'm so proud of you, Marc.

478
00:28:56.783 --> 00:28:59.158
Now just stay with me
for one second, okay?

479
00:28:59.491 --> 00:29:01.283
I want you to consider this.

480
00:29:01.366 --> 00:29:03.575
Do you think you created Steven

481
00:29:04.408 --> 00:29:08.658
to hide from all of the awful things
you feel you've done in your life,

482
00:29:08.866 --> 00:29:11.825
or do you think Steven created Marc
to punish the world

483
00:29:11.908 --> 00:29:13.575
for what your mother did to you?

484
00:29:17.075 --> 00:29:18.116
Do you know?

485
00:29:19.741 --> 00:29:20.866
Can you remember?

486
00:29:21.950 --> 00:29:25.658
There's only one way to know.

487
00:29:26.950 --> 00:29:29.158
You're gonna have to open up to Steven.

488
00:29:30.616 --> 00:29:33.491
There can be no progress
without understanding.

489
00:29:34.950 --> 00:29:36.116
Can you do that?

490
00:29:37.533 --> 00:29:39.491
Can you open up to Steven?

491
00:29:52.866 --> 00:29:56.741
I don't... This is my room.

492
00:29:57.325 --> 00:29:59.616
I remember some things,
but I don't remember this.

493
00:30:00.491 --> 00:30:02.033
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

494
00:30:03.200 --> 00:30:05.116
YOUNG MARC: It's not Mom. It's not my mom.

495
00:30:06.950 --> 00:30:08.158
It's not my mom.

496
00:30:08.991 --> 00:30:10.616
- It's not my mom.
- (KNOCKING CONTINUES)

497
00:30:11.075 --> 00:30:12.408
WENDY: Marc, open this door.

498
00:30:12.700 --> 00:30:14.533
Open this door right now.

499
00:30:14.616 --> 00:30:15.866
It's not my mom.

500
00:30:16.908 --> 00:30:18.450
- Open this door.
- It's not my mom.

501
00:30:19.075 --> 00:30:20.533
It's not my mom.

502
00:30:26.033 --> 00:30:29.033
(IN BRITISH ACCENT) Bloody hell.
Look at the state of this place.

503
00:30:30.116 --> 00:30:32.575
Better sort it out before Mum sees it.

504
00:30:34.533 --> 00:30:37.283
WENDY: Marc, open this door right now!

505
00:30:42.533 --> 00:30:43.866
(BANGING ON DOOR)

506
00:30:45.033 --> 00:30:49.700
STEVEN: "When danger is near,
Steven Grant has no fear."

507
00:30:53.575 --> 00:30:54.741
You made me up.

508
00:30:55.241 --> 00:30:57.866
- (BANGING CONTINUES)
- WENDY: Open this door right now!

509
00:31:02.075 --> 00:31:03.616
You're gonna learn

510
00:31:05.491 --> 00:31:06.658
to listen.

511
00:31:13.200 --> 00:31:15.950
Why do you have to make me do this?

512
00:31:16.033 --> 00:31:17.241
I wanna see what she did.

513
00:31:17.325 --> 00:31:18.445
WENDY: You disgusting human.

514
00:31:18.491 --> 00:31:20.658
You do not need to see that.

515
00:31:20.741 --> 00:31:22.075
That's the whole point of you.

516
00:31:25.366 --> 00:31:26.408
(GROANS)

517
00:31:27.491 --> 00:31:29.075
The point of me?

518
00:31:29.741 --> 00:31:31.908
The point of me?
What? To be your stress ball?

519
00:31:33.116 --> 00:31:35.033
All this time
I thought I was the original,

520
00:31:36.033 --> 00:31:37.783
but I'm just something that you made up.

521
00:31:38.450 --> 00:31:39.575
You've got to live

522
00:31:40.616 --> 00:31:45.575
a happy, simple, normal life.
You understand?

523
00:31:45.658 --> 00:31:47.366
But it was all a lie, wasn't it?

524
00:31:47.616 --> 00:31:48.616
So what?

525
00:31:49.366 --> 00:31:50.491
What does it matter?

526
00:31:50.783 --> 00:31:52.408
What? You wanna remember the truth?

527
00:31:52.866 --> 00:31:56.116
That you had a mother that beats you?
That hated you?

528
00:31:56.200 --> 00:31:58.200
That made your life a living hell?

529
00:31:58.283 --> 00:32:00.325
You're lying.
You're just trying to upset me.

530
00:32:00.408 --> 00:32:03.075
But you've gotten to live
thinking that she loved you.

531
00:32:03.408 --> 00:32:06.450
That she was kind. That she's still alive!

532
00:32:09.741 --> 00:32:10.825
What?

533
00:32:11.366 --> 00:32:12.533
What are you talking about?

534
00:32:12.616 --> 00:32:15.658
She's alive. I speak to her every day.
What are you talking about?

535
00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.116
Dad called me after all these years,

536
00:32:18.700 --> 00:32:21.741
about her Shiva, and I couldn't do it.

537
00:32:21.825 --> 00:32:25.908
No, this is all wrong.
This is... No, this is all wrong.

538
00:32:25.991 --> 00:32:27.866
- Steven, I'm sorry.
- Oh, no, no, no.

539
00:32:27.950 --> 00:32:30.366
No, no, no. No, thank you.

540
00:32:30.450 --> 00:32:33.533
- No. Let me out, let me out!
- Calm down. It's all right. It's okay.

541
00:32:33.616 --> 00:32:35.575
Let me out, let me out! (GRUNTS)

542
00:32:37.408 --> 00:32:40.158
God. I'm so sorry. Sorry...

543
00:32:40.283 --> 00:32:42.200
God. I'm so sorry. Sorry...

544
00:32:42.575 --> 00:32:45.700
You gave me a real start there.
Gave you a bit of a wash, didn't I?

545
00:32:46.158 --> 00:32:47.200
Steven?

546
00:32:48.950 --> 00:32:50.825
Hold on a minute. What's this...

547
00:32:51.741 --> 00:32:53.075
It's good to see you again.

548
00:32:53.158 --> 00:32:54.950
What is this? Is this some kind of test?

549
00:32:56.366 --> 00:32:57.866
I recognize this place.

550
00:32:58.075 --> 00:32:59.116
What's this?

551
00:32:59.783 --> 00:33:02.866
- Steven, I'm your doctor. Remember?
- (SCOFFS) You're my doctor?

552
00:33:03.200 --> 00:33:05.825
- I'm here to help you.
- Dr. Harrow, yeah, is it?

553
00:33:05.908 --> 00:33:07.908
- That's right.
- Oh, yeah, look at that.

554
00:33:08.241 --> 00:33:09.491
Well...

555
00:33:09.950 --> 00:33:11.950
You've really gone up in the world,
haven't you?

556
00:33:12.033 --> 00:33:14.741
I was beginning to worry we might
never speak again.

557
00:33:17.075 --> 00:33:21.450
It's so strange. The little haircut.
Little silly 'tache there.

558
00:33:22.700 --> 00:33:24.700
It's very Ned Flanders.

559
00:33:25.283 --> 00:33:27.991
- Steven.
- What's Taweret up to now?

560
00:33:28.950 --> 00:33:31.575
It's my fault. I asked Marc
to open up to you.

561
00:33:31.658 --> 00:33:33.658
Did he get a chance to speak with you?

562
00:33:35.116 --> 00:33:36.533
Yeah, well, he...

563
00:33:37.700 --> 00:33:39.366
He lied to me. That's what he did.

564
00:33:39.450 --> 00:33:42.575
Mmm-hmm. And what do you feel
that he lied to you about?

565
00:33:43.408 --> 00:33:44.950
Oh. Nosy.

566
00:33:46.241 --> 00:33:49.075
No, it's just...
Steven, when you first came in here,

567
00:33:49.158 --> 00:33:52.075
I was worried you were never
gonna be able to acknowledge Marc.

568
00:33:52.158 --> 00:33:53.491
What do you mean we're not...

569
00:33:54.616 --> 00:33:55.825
I brought us here?

570
00:33:57.825 --> 00:33:59.158
After your mother passed.

571
00:33:59.658 --> 00:34:01.658
Oi. Don't say that.

572
00:34:02.241 --> 00:34:03.616
That's not true.

573
00:34:04.033 --> 00:34:05.033
That's not true.

574
00:34:05.116 --> 00:34:06.241
Oh, I'm so... I must...

575
00:34:06.366 --> 00:34:08.575
You having a laugh as well?
I don't wanna hear it.

576
00:34:08.658 --> 00:34:10.783
- Steven, I must be mistaken.
- My mother is alive.

577
00:34:10.866 --> 00:34:13.283
You say that again,
I will freak out! I promise.

578
00:34:13.366 --> 00:34:14.700
I must be mistaken. Okay?

579
00:34:14.783 --> 00:34:18.241
Would you like to speak with her?
Why don't we call her?

580
00:34:18.700 --> 00:34:19.950
You don't have her number.

581
00:34:20.033 --> 00:34:21.616
Yeah, we have it on file.

582
00:34:21.700 --> 00:34:24.200
- Hold on, let me just get Dylan.
- No, don't do that.

583
00:34:24.283 --> 00:34:25.366
It'll take two seconds.

584
00:34:25.450 --> 00:34:26.741
Don't bother her.

585
00:34:26.825 --> 00:34:29.908
Hey, Dylan. Yeah.
Could you call Mrs. Grant, please?

586
00:34:29.991 --> 00:34:31.741
She screens her calls. She won't answer.

587
00:34:31.825 --> 00:34:34.533
- She's afraid of tele salespeople.
- She'll wanna talk to you.

588
00:34:34.616 --> 00:34:36.950
I'm sure of it. She's getting the number.

589
00:34:37.033 --> 00:34:38.075
Don't do that.

590
00:34:38.158 --> 00:34:40.033
Okay, okay. Thank you.

591
00:34:40.116 --> 00:34:41.783
- Please don't do that.
- It's ringing.

592
00:34:41.866 --> 00:34:43.283
Don't bother her, please.

593
00:34:43.366 --> 00:34:47.200
Uh, hello, Mrs. Grant.
Yes, this is Dr. Harrow.

594
00:34:47.283 --> 00:34:48.450
Mmm-hmm.

595
00:34:49.241 --> 00:34:51.325
Steven's here.
He'd like to speak with you.

596
00:34:52.366 --> 00:34:55.575
Steven, would you like to speak
to your mum?

597
00:35:05.991 --> 00:35:07.200
My mum...

598
00:35:11.033 --> 00:35:12.116
(SOFTLY) My mum is dead.

599
00:35:21.033 --> 00:35:22.200
My mum is dead.

600
00:36:05.241 --> 00:36:06.700
MARC: No, no. Not gonna do it.

601
00:36:07.866 --> 00:36:09.908
I'm not giving you that satisfaction.

602
00:36:37.783 --> 00:36:38.866
I'm so sorry.

603
00:36:42.283 --> 00:36:43.950
I'm so sorry.

604
00:36:44.075 --> 00:36:45.575
(SOBBING)

605
00:37:03.116 --> 00:37:04.325
(GRUNTS)

606
00:37:08.033 --> 00:37:09.033
(AS STEVEN) What...

607
00:37:09.866 --> 00:37:11.075
Where am I?

608
00:37:14.575 --> 00:37:15.783
Bloody hell, what...

609
00:37:18.491 --> 00:37:20.658
Oh, bollocks.

610
00:37:21.283 --> 00:37:22.575
Not again.

611
00:37:23.450 --> 00:37:25.325
Heya, Mum. Hey, you all right?

612
00:37:25.491 --> 00:37:26.491
Yeah, um...

613
00:37:26.908 --> 00:37:31.450
(CHUCKLES) Would you believe it?
I am totally lost again.

614
00:37:31.533 --> 00:37:34.200
I don't know where I am.
What an absolute muppet!

615
00:37:34.741 --> 00:37:37.366
No, I know I did it again,
but I don't know.

616
00:37:37.450 --> 00:37:38.908
I'm looking down a street...

617
00:37:40.033 --> 00:37:42.491
Kinda looks a bit like Mayfair. I think...

618
00:37:42.575 --> 00:37:44.783
Oh, they're driving
on the wrong side. Sorry.

619
00:37:44.866 --> 00:37:47.658
MARC: This is it. Mom's death
and Shiva two months ago.

620
00:37:48.200 --> 00:37:51.116
This was the moment our lives
started bleeding into each other.

621
00:37:51.200 --> 00:37:53.950
Milwaukee... Milwaukee Avenue?
Does that sound familiar?

622
00:37:54.033 --> 00:37:55.450
I couldn't...

623
00:37:56.408 --> 00:37:58.783
I just couldn't...
I couldn't face that again.

624
00:38:00.741 --> 00:38:02.241
All the things I'd done...

625
00:38:02.325 --> 00:38:03.491
Marc,

626
00:38:04.200 --> 00:38:07.241
all those horrible things
that she said to you,

627
00:38:07.325 --> 00:38:09.408
she was wrong. It wasn't your fault.

628
00:38:11.658 --> 00:38:14.158
I shouldn't have brought him in the cave.

629
00:38:14.325 --> 00:38:15.325
Hey.

630
00:38:16.658 --> 00:38:19.616
Hey. You were just a child.

631
00:38:21.866 --> 00:38:23.200
It wasn't your fault.

632
00:38:30.241 --> 00:38:31.658
(RUMBLING)

633
00:38:32.575 --> 00:38:34.116
Hey, do you feel that?

634
00:38:35.741 --> 00:38:37.366
I think we just stopped.

635
00:38:38.283 --> 00:38:39.366
The Gates.

636
00:38:40.325 --> 00:38:43.116
The Gates of Osiris. Come on. Hurry.

637
00:38:46.116 --> 00:38:47.825
Taweret, what's happening?

638
00:38:47.908 --> 00:38:50.783
TAWERET: I've never seen the gates
to the world above so close.

639
00:38:51.033 --> 00:38:52.075
MARC: How do we open them?

640
00:38:52.158 --> 00:38:54.450
I'm so sorry. Your Scales never balanced.

641
00:38:54.533 --> 00:38:58.200
Our journey's come to an end.
I cannot stop the inevitable.

642
00:38:58.283 --> 00:39:00.241
I was really rooting for you guys,

643
00:39:00.325 --> 00:39:04.116
but the unbalanced souls of the Duat
now must claim yours.

644
00:39:27.741 --> 00:39:29.741
Marc, they don't look very friendly.

645
00:39:29.866 --> 00:39:31.325
Hide. Hide.

646
00:39:33.575 --> 00:39:36.616
Gabon. New York, Dubai.

647
00:39:38.616 --> 00:39:40.075
STEVEN: Watch out!

648
00:39:44.575 --> 00:39:45.825
(GRUNTS)

649
00:39:48.783 --> 00:39:49.825
Oh, no!

650
00:39:51.533 --> 00:39:52.866
Taweret!

651
00:39:53.783 --> 00:39:55.158
(SCREAMING)

652
00:39:57.033 --> 00:39:58.075
No!

653
00:40:16.616 --> 00:40:17.866
Oh, God.

654
00:40:21.658 --> 00:40:24.658
Marc, you've got this.

655
00:40:26.158 --> 00:40:27.283
But if I'm you...

656
00:40:29.366 --> 00:40:30.825
It means I've got this, too.

657
00:40:32.491 --> 00:40:34.075
(YELLS)

658
00:40:41.366 --> 00:40:42.575
Six!

659
00:40:43.616 --> 00:40:45.158
I prefer cricket.

660
00:40:55.741 --> 00:40:59.658
(GRUNTING)

661
00:41:01.908 --> 00:41:02.908
Ow!

662
00:41:07.158 --> 00:41:08.700
No! No!

663
00:41:09.783 --> 00:41:11.783
Marc! Marc, no!

664
00:41:18.200 --> 00:41:19.783
Steven!

665
00:41:19.866 --> 00:41:21.075
Steven!

666
00:41:23.075 --> 00:41:24.491
Steven!

667
00:41:24.908 --> 00:41:26.075
(STEVEN GROANS)

668
00:41:28.825 --> 00:41:30.033
Steven!

669
00:41:30.825 --> 00:41:33.408
No, wait. Wait. Wait!

670
00:41:33.991 --> 00:41:36.158
- Wait!
- Steven! Run!

671
00:41:36.366 --> 00:41:37.616
- Wait!
- Wait, he's coming!

672
00:41:37.908 --> 00:41:39.825
Keep... Stop the boat. Stop the boat!

673
00:41:39.950 --> 00:41:42.325
STEVEN: Wait! Wait!

674
00:41:45.033 --> 00:41:46.075
Oh, God.

675
00:41:46.658 --> 00:41:48.575
- Steven!
- Wait...

676
00:41:49.575 --> 00:41:52.325
No, no, no! Steven!

677
00:41:52.408 --> 00:41:53.408
(GROANS)

678
00:42:06.658 --> 00:42:08.908
Stop the boat! Stop the boat!

679
00:42:10.283 --> 00:42:11.366
(METAL CLINKS)

680
00:42:11.825 --> 00:42:14.908
TAWERET: (GASPS)
Your Scales are balanced.

